Consider a gas contained in the cylinder-piston arrangement shown in Figure 1.1. The gas is pure nitrogen ($N_2$) with a mass of 1.60 g and is in equilibrium with its surroundings. The gas is initially at standard temperature and pressure, with $P = 101$ kPa and $T = 0^degree C$. 

The piston is now moved, slowly enough so that equilibrium with the surroundings is maintained, until its pressure reaches 120 kPa. What are the initial volume ($V_1$) and final volume ($V_2$) of the gas?

#set page(width: a_width, height: auto, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
$V_1 = 0.0013 " m"^3$ and $V_2 = 0.0011 " m"^3$
